So bad and may I say it was not worth the money  Update I want to give a new review to this place, I want to thank the manager who reach out who went above and beyond to help me with the issues that came from Uber eats. I say don’t order from Uber eats as it may take so much time to get a crepe and it may not look tasty and not taste as well.

Sofi's is easily the best crêperie in Baltimore.  What that's ultimately saying I leave as an exercise to the reader.  It's a small place, and service can be a little slow only because they can only make 2 crepes at a time.  Plan ahead if you're going to a movie at The Charles.  Crepe quality is also often sensitive to the crepe engineer on duty.  One last thing: replace the caramel on any crepe with the house -made butterscotch; thank me later.

I'm a small-business woman and mother of a toddler. Little I need to say I have no time to eat, less to write a review!  I'm taking a breakfast break while digesting and packing a lunch for my kid to write this.  If you are busy professional, business person, student, mom, broke, pay-check-to-pay-check, barely surviving run to Sofie's Crepes! You will find you the best, healthiest, delicious, refined, made-to-order (as fresh as the originals), huuuugggeee portion (2 meals for myself) for only $8 no drinks crepe only.  I stumble upon this jewel by mere accident! I didn't research it online nor bought the Baltimore magazine. My go to "find best restaurants in town". I just follow the wisdom of a 9 y.o. Who convinced ME that a French crepe tasted and was healthier than a burger and fries for lunch. The wisdom of babies...
